    "instruction": "Analyze log.csv as follows:\n1) Compute global thresholds (P95 and P5) per (cmdb_id, log_name) across the entire log.csv (do NOT filter by time before computing thresholds).\n2) Filter log rows to the incident window 2021-03-23 23:00:00 CST — 2021-03-23 23:30:00 CST.\n3) For cmdb_ids of interest [MG02, MG01, Tomcat03, Tomcat04, Tomcat01, Tomcat02], produce a compact aggregate per (cmdb_id, log_name) with: cmdb_id, log_name, count_in_window, anomalies_count (value >= p95 OR value <= p5), earliest_anomaly_ts, max_value_in_window, min_value_in_window, p95, p5, direction (\"high\" or \"low\" by largest relative breach), max_relative_deviation (same formula as used for metrics/traces).\n4) Return the total number of (cmdb_id, log_name) combos with anomalies_count > 0 for these components and the top 20 rows ordered by max_relative_deviation descending. Keep output compact and limit rows to at most 20."
}

